commits.message: Modify suspension spring for the HMMWV vehicle in the ChronoModels library
Modify demo_VEH_SPHTerrain_WheeledVehicle to illustrate different ways of initializing SPHTerrain
Unify mechanism to specify a visualization grid across different systems
Rename SPHTerrain to CRMTerrain
Rename Chrono::Vehicle model RCCar to ARTcar
Update ChangeLog file
Fix list of exported include headers from the Chrono::Parsers module
Get & Set Irrlicht creation parameters and rendering window id
Expose optional support in various Chrono modules through the project configuration script
Merge branch 'main' of https://github.com/projectchrono/chrono
Make the utility function SetChronoSolver to all demos
Fix indexing bug in ChLoadBodyTorque
Re-introduce irrlicht modifications of commit 3938d4209
Minor cleanup/fixes
Extend mechanism for external loads on a vehicle chassis to also allow applying external torques
Eliminate assert in Bullet function
Clean up ChLoadXYZnode classes

Modify mechanism for applying SCM terrain forces to contactables (bodies or FEA nodes).

- instead of creating a ChLoad for each hit SCM grid node, use the accumulated forces and torques to create one ChLoad per contactable
- this reduces the cost of SCM force evaluation to almost half
- note however, that the SCM computational bottleneck is elswhere (namely in ray intersection tests)
Modify demo for single wheel test rig to properly deal with flexible tires on deformable (SCM) terrain
Add new templates for solid Panhard suspensions
Add model and data files for the Mercedes G-500 vehicle
Added CastTo for sensor types. Updated ChROSLidarHandler to use reserve rather than resize
Eliminate assert in Bullet function
Clean up ChLoadXYZnode classes
